1.Install
  Prerequisites:
  -> UEFI boot mode enabled
  -> Secure Boot disabled during installation
  -> At least 1.5GB RAM (if using official NixOS Minimal ISO)
  -> At least 3.0GB RAM (if using official NixOS Graphical ISO)
    $ git clone <repo>
    $ sudo nixos-generate-config --no-filesystems --show-hardware-config > ./nixos/hardware.nix
  Edit the disk configuration to match your system
    $ vim ./nixos/modules/disko.nix
    $ sudo nix-shell -p disko --run "disko -m destroy,format,mount ./nixos/modules/disko.nix"
  Preventing memory shortage
    $ sudo swapon /mnt/swap/swapfile
  Generate Secure Boot Keys
    $ sudo nix-shell -p sbctl --run "sbctl create-keys"
    $ sudo mv /var/lib/sbctl /mnt/persist/lanzaboote
  Install NixOS
    $ sudo mkdir -p /mnt/persist/home/saya/Projects
    $ sudo cp -r ./nixos /mnt/persist/home/saya/Projects
    $ sudo nixos-install --flake /mnt/persist/home/saya/Projects/nixos#Gamma
    $ reboot
  The default username is “saya”, and the password is “none”

2.Secure Boot
  Enter Secure Boot Setup Mode
  > Then refer to <https://nix-community.github.io/lanzaboote/getting-started/enable-secure-boot.html>
    $ sudo mount -o bind /persist/lanzaboote /var/lib/sbctl
    $ sudo nix run nixpkgs#sbctl -- enroll-keys
  Enable Secure Boot

3.Automatic LUKS decryption with TPM 2.0
    $ sudo systemd-cryptenroll --tpm2-device=auto --tpm2-pcrs=0+7 /dev/disk/by-uuid/<YOUR-PARTITION-UUID>
